The paper discusses neural network architectures that are motivated by Fourier series and integrals, which are commonly used in signal processing and image analysis. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
